    "# Staten Island Flood Risk Analysis\n",
    "## Using Unsupervised Learning for Pattern Detection and Risk Assessment\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook analyzes flood sensor data from Staten Island to:\n",
    "1. Identify high-risk areas\n",
    "2. Detect flood patterns\n",
    "3. Assess vulnerability\n",
    "4. Generate risk predictions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [

    "def load_and_process_data(filepath):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Load and preprocess the flood sensor data.\"\"\"\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        # Load data\n",
    "        df = pd.read_csv(filepath)\n",
    "        df['Time'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Time'])\n",
    "        df.set_index('Time', inplace=True)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Create area-specific dataframes\n",
    "        area_dfs = {}\n",
    "        for area, info in STATEN_ISLAND_AREAS.items():\n",
    "            area_dfs[area] = df[info['sensors']]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        print(f\"Data loaded successfully: {df.shape[0]} timestamps, {df.shape[1]} sensors\")\n",
    "        return df, area_dfs\n",
    "    \n",
    "    except Exception as e:\n",
    "        print(f\"Error loading data: {e}\")\n",
    "        return None, None\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load the data\n",
    "df, area_dfs = load_and_process_data('flood_sensor_data_Zhang.csv')\n",
    "\n",
    "if df is not None:\n",
    "    print(\"\\nFirst few rows of the data:\")\n",
    "    display(df.head())\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"\\nBasic statistics:\")\n",
    "    display(df.describe())"
   ]
  },

    "def analyze_sensor_data(df, area_dfs):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Perform initial analysis of sensor data.\"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Overall sensor correlation heatmap\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))\n",
    "    sns.heatmap(df.corr(), annot=True, cmap='coolwarm', center=0)\n",
    "    plt.title('Sensor Correlation Matrix')\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Area-wise analysis\n",
    "    for area, data in area_dfs.items():\n",
    "        fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(15, 5))\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Daily averages\n",
    "        daily_avg = data.resample('D').mean()\n",
    "        daily_avg.plot(ax=ax1)\n",
    "        ax1.set_title(f'{area} - Daily Average Flood Levels')\n",
    "        ax1.set_xlabel('Date')\n",
    "        ax1.set_ylabel('Flood Level')\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Distribution\n",
    "        for column in data.columns:\n",
    "            sns.kdeplot(data=data[column], ax=ax2, label=column)\n",
    "        ax2.set_title(f'{area} - Flood Level Distribution')\n",
    "        ax2.set_xlabel('Flood Level')\n",
    "        \n",
    "        plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "        plt.show()\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Print summary statistics\n",
    "        print(f\"\\nSummary Statistics for {area}:\")\n",
    "        display(data.describe())\n",
    "\n",
    "analyze_sensor_data(df, area_dfs)"
   ]
  }
